  "prompt": "Is there any management quota at PCCOE Pune? What are the fees?",
  "response": "Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering (PCCOE) in Pune, like many engineering colleges, may have a management quota in place, which allows a certain percentage of seats to be filled at the discretion of the management. However, specific details regarding the number of seats, the exact process, and the fees under the management quota can vary and may change from year to year.\n\nThe fees for a management quota seat are typically higher than the fees for seats filled through other quotas (such as merit or reservation quotas). The amount can vary based on various factors, including the course, demand, and policies of the institution.\n\nFor precise and up-to-date information on the availability of management quota seats and their fees at PCCOE Pune, it's best to directly contact the admissions office of the college or visit their official website.",
